{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "SPTAG follows a DC approach and is based on multiple existing works.",
    "It selects small dataset samples on which it builds either K-D Trees [17] or Balanced K-means Trees [95].",
    "These strutures will be used for seed selection during query answering.",
    "Then it clusters the full dataset using multiple hierarchical random divisions of TP Trees [141], builds an exact k-NN graph on each cluster (i.e., leaf) and refines each graph using ND.",
    "The graphs are merged into one large graph index for query processing."
  ],
